immPort-Study.title: Immport-study element schema
immPort-Study.description: Immport-study element schema autogenerated by the CEDAR Template Editor

_ui.title: ImmPort-Study
_ui.description: ImmPort Study element

_ui.title: Brief Title
_ui.description: The brief title serves as a working title for a study

_ui.title: User Def Study ID
_ui.description: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded

_ui.title: Official Title
_ui.description: The official study title may be the same as the brief title, but is often more descriptive

_ui.title: Detailed Description
_ui.description: Summarize the goals, methods and results of the study

_ui.title: Hypothesis
_ui.description: The explanatory proposition(s) being tested by the research study

_ui.title: Objectives
_ui.description: The goals of the research study

_ui.title: Endpoints
_ui.description: Endpoints include assessments, lab tests and assays that are part of a study design

_ui.title: Sponsoring Organization
_ui.description: The organization that provides funding and support for the study

_ui.title: Target Enrollment
_ui.description: The number of subjects proposed to be enrolled in the study

_ui.title: Condition Studied
_ui.description: A short description of what is being researched or evaluated in the study (e.g. influenza vaccine)

_ui.title: Minimum Age
_ui.description: The minimum age of subjects enrolled in the study

_ui.title: Maximum Age
_ui.description: The maximum age of subjects enrolled in the study

_ui.title: Age Unit
_ui.description: The unit of time used to describe the subject's age in the study

_ui.title: Intervention Agent
_ui.description: IA brief description of the study's interventional component (e.g. influenza vaccine)

_ui.title: ImmPort-ArmOrCohort
_ui.description: ImmPort ArmOrCohort element

_ui.title: User Def Arm Or Cohort ID
_ui.description: The arm or cohort user defined ID is an identifier chosen by the data provider to refer to a subject grouping in the study document. This ID may be referenced by other data records (e.g. subjects). The user defined ID is not shared

_ui.title: Name
_ui.description: The arm or cohort name is an alternate identifier that is visible when the study is shared

_ui.title: Description
_ui.description: The description should expand any abbreviations used in the arm or cohort name

_ui.title: Population Selection Rule
_ui.description: Describe how subjects were assigned to arms or cohorts

_ui.title: Sort Order
_ui.description: The sort order column controls the order in which arms or Cohorts are listed in the ImmPort display

_ui.title: Type
_ui.description: Example clinical study values: Observational, Experimental, Active Comparator, Placebo Comparator, Sham Comparator

_ui.title: ImmPort-StudyPersonnel
_ui.description: An ImmPort StudyPersonnel element

_ui.title: User Def Study Personnel ID
_ui.description: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded

_ui.title: Honorific
_ui.description: Usually, the education achievement level of the person

_ui.title: Last Name
_ui.description: The last name of the study personnel being described

_ui.title: First Name
_ui.description: The first name of the study personnel being described

_ui.title: Suffixes
_ui.description: Suffixes that are part of the study personnel's name being described

_ui.title: Organization
_ui.description: The organization with whom the study personnel being described is affiliated

_ui.title: Email
_ui.description: Contact information of the study personnel being described

_ui.title: Title In Study
_ui.description: The role the personnel play in the study as defined by the research team

_ui.title: Site Name
_ui.description: Enter the site name if there is a need to further differentiate the affiliation of the study personnel from the Organization

_ui.title: ImmPort-Period
_ui.description: An ImmPort Period element

_ui.title: User Def Period ID
_ui.description: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded

_ui.title: Title
_ui.description: The period title is an alternate identifier that is visible when the protocol is shared

_ui.title: Order Number
_ui.description: The order of the period within a study

_ui.title: ImmPort-PlannedVisit
_ui.description: An ImmPort PlannedVisit element

_ui.title: User Def Planned Visit ID
_ui.description: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded

_ui.title: Visit Name
_ui.description: The visit name is an alternate identifier that is visible when the protocol is shared

_ui.title: Visit Order Number
_ui.description: The order of the visit within the study design schedule

_ui.title: User Def Period ID
_ui.description: Enter the user defined period ID as defined in the 'period' block of the study design

_ui.title: Min Start Day
_ui.description: The minimum start day for a visit as defined in the study schedule

_ui.title: Max Start Day
_ui.description: The maximum start day for a visit as defined in the study schedule

_ui.title: End Rule
_ui.description: Enter an end rule only if it is more interesting than "subject has arrived for a scheduled visit"

_ui.title: ImmPort-InclusionExclusion
_ui.description: An ImmPort InclusionExclusion element

_ui.title: User Def Criterion ID
_ui.description: The identifier should be unique to the ImmPort workspace to which the data will be uploaded

_ui.title: Criterion
_ui.description: The criterion describes the parameter used to decide if a subject may be enrolled in a study

_ui.title: ImmPort-StudyFile
_ui.description: An ImmPort StudyFile element

_ui.title: FileName
_ui.description: The name of the file, including file extension, that is to be linked to the study. The file size name limit is 250 characters. For a given study, all file names for study_file must be unique.

_ui.title: Description
_ui.description: A brief description of the file

_ui.title: ImmPort-StudyLink
_ui.description: An ImmPort StudyLink element

_ui.title: Link Name
_ui.description: The name of the website to which the link refers

_ui.title: Link Value
_ui.description: Define websites that are linked to the study. Insert rows in the template to define additional websites linked to the study.

_ui.title: ImmPort-StudyPubmedInfo
_ui.description: An ImmPort StudyPubmedInfo element

_ui.title: Pubmed ID
_ui.description: The Pubmed or PubMedCentral identifier of an article that includes data from this study

_ui.title: Pubmed Title
_ui.description: The title of an article that includes data from this study

_ui.title: Journal
_ui.description: The journal name that publishes an article that includes data from this study

_ui.title: Year
_ui.description: The article publication year

_ui.title: Month
_ui.description: The article publication month

_ui.title: Issue
_ui.description: The journal's issue number

_ui.title: Pages
_ui.description: The journal's page number

_ui.title: Author
_ui.description: The article's authors
